Installation
To run the freelancer/jobseeker website locally, follow these steps:

Clone the repository: git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo.git
Navigate to the project directory: cd your-repo
Open the index.html file in a web browser.
Usage
Upon opening the website, users can perform the following actions:

Create a new profile: Users can register and create their freelancer/jobseeker profile by providing relevant information such as personal details, skills, experience, and portfolio.
Browse job listings: Users can view available job listings posted by clients/employers.
Apply for jobs: Users can apply for jobs by submitting their profiles and portfolios to potential clients/employers.
Connect with clients/employers: Users can communicate with clients/employers through the messaging system provided on the platform.
Contributing
We welcome contributions to enhance the freelancer/jobseeker website. To contribute, please follow these steps:

Fork the repository.
Create a new branch: git checkout -b feature/your-feature
Make your changes and commit them: git commit -am 'Add your feature'
Push to the branch: git push origin feature/your-feature
Create a new Pull Request.


